**APPENDIX II**

### *LIST OF THE CHIEF UPANISHADS*

The following list gives the names of the most ancient and important
Upanishads, together with the contractions used for them in the
preceding pages. The canon generally accepted in modern India contains
108 Upanishads; most of these are however comparatively late and
distinctly sectarian (later Vedāntī, Vishṇuite, Śivaite, Yogī, Sannyāsī,
etc.).

